# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Lychee link checker — exclusion patterns (regex, one per line)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Each line is a regex matched against the URL.
# Used by both PR job (--offline) and weekly full check.

# ───── Localhost / loopback (development URLs in code examples) ─────
^https?://localhost
^https?://127\.0\.0\.1
^https?://0\.0\.0\.0

# ───── Placeholder URLs in code examples / docs ─────
example\.com
example\.org
yourcompany\.

# ───── Internal Docker hostnames (referenced in nginx.conf, compose) ─────
^https?://(backend|frontend|nginx|postgres|redis|app|db):\d+

# ───── Private / staging hosts that aren't publicly reachable ─────
\.internal/
\.local(/|$)

# ───── Known-flaky external sources (rate-limit aggressive, OK to skip) ─────
# Add specific URLs here as link rot is detected, with comment explaining why.
# Example:
# ^https://twitter\.com/.*  # Twitter blocks all bot traffic in 2026
